  <description><![CDATA[<p>Royal Hotel Sanremo is part of the Leading Hotels of the World group and is named after the seaside town of <a data-udi="umb://document/7dda8a7d883a4ead816b9eb9cb85b733" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7dda8a7d883a4ead816b9eb9cb85b733}" title="Sanremo">Sanremo</a> in which it stands. The hotel is in the style of traditional grand Italian seaside hotels with impressively large rooms, high ceilings and classic decor. It is centrally located across the road from the beach where it has sunbeds and umbrellas for your relaxation (payable locally from 2020).</p>
<p>The hotel has a total of three restaurants serving a variety of high class cuisine. Restaurant Il Giardino is opened during the summer months offering a gourmet menu that can be enjoyed al fresco, surrounded by the lush gardens and overlooking the Mediterranean Sea. With panoramic bay windows offering breath-taking views of the Mediterranean Sea, the Fiori di Murano restaurant decorated with delicate Murano glass chandeliers serves an impressive à la carte menu. The restaurant Corallina is the ideal option for lunch or snacks. An buffet offering an array of fresh ingredients with grilled fish and meats. The restaurant also caters for children with their own menu that includes pizza and chips. </p>
<p>Indulge in the exclusive selection of spa services and facilities provided in the Royal Wellness Centre. The spa is opened each day and facilities include a hydromassage pool, sauna and a fitness room. </p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 50 mins from Genoa or 1 hour from Nice. Private transfers included.</p>]]></description>
